from prior to comparison

Haowei Lee

12/14/2021

Import libraries

library(rethinking)
Review of prior pediction using the milk data of chapter 5

Import data

# Import the data
data(rugged) # 5.27 @ 148
d <- rugged
# precis(d)  # inspect the data

Use log to get the logged outcome

d$log_gdp <- log(d$rgdppc_2000)

Use complete.cases to filter the data, dropping NA value at rgdppc_2000

dd <- d[complete.cases(d$rgdppc_2000),]

rescale variables

dd$log_gdp_std <- dd$log_gdp / mean(dd$log_gdp)
dd$rugged_std <- dd$rugged / max(dd$rugged)

Use quap to build a model

m8.1_a <- quap(
  alist(
    log_gdp_std ~ dnorm(mu, sigma),
    mu <- a + b*(rugged_std - 0.215),
    a ~ dnorm(1, 1),
    b ~ dnorm(0, 1),
    sigma ~ dexp(1)
  ), data = dd
)

Use extract.prior to retrieve prior from our model

set.seed(7)
prior_a <- extract.prior(m8.1_a)

Plot the prior prediction using the prior we just got

# set up the plot dimensions
plot( NULL , xlim=c(0,1) , ylim=c(0.5,1.5) ,
    xlab="ruggedness" , ylab="log GDP" )
abline( h=min(dd$log_gdp_std) , lty=2 )
abline( h=max(dd$log_gdp_std) , lty=2 )

# draw 50 lines from the prior
rugged_seq <- seq( from=-0.1 , to=1.1 , length.out=30 )
mu <- link( m8.1_a , post=prior_a , data=data.frame(rugged_std=rugged_seq) )
for ( i in 1:50 ) lines( rugged_seq , mu[i,] , col=col.alpha("black",0.3) )

revise the prior

m8.1_b <- quap(
    alist(
        log_gdp_std ~ dnorm( mu , sigma ) ,
        mu <- a + b*( rugged_std - 0.215 ) ,
        a ~ dnorm( 1 , 0.1 ) ,
        b ~ dnorm( 0 , 0.3 ) ,
        sigma ~ dexp(1)
    ) , data=dd )

Plot the prior prediction using the prior we just got

# extract the new priors
set.seed(7)
prior_b <- extract.prior(m8.1_b) 

# set up the plot dimensions
plot( NULL , xlim=c(0,1) , ylim=c(0.5,1.5) ,
    xlab="ruggedness" , ylab="log GDP" )
abline( h=min(dd$log_gdp_std) , lty=2 )
abline( h=max(dd$log_gdp_std) , lty=2 )

# draw 50 lines from the prior
rugged_seq <- seq( from=-0.1 , to=1.1 , length.out=30 )
mu <- link( m8.1_b , post=prior_b , data=data.frame(rugged_std=rugged_seq) )
for ( i in 1:50 ) lines( rugged_seq , mu[i,] , col=col.alpha("black",0.3) )

Deal with categorical variable

# make variable to index Africa (1) or not (2)
dd$cid <- ifelse( dd$cont_africa==1 , 1 , 2 )

Construct the second model

m8.2 <- quap(
    alist(
        log_gdp_std ~ dnorm( mu , sigma ) ,
        mu <- a[cid] + b*( rugged_std - 0.215 ) ,
        a[cid] ~ dnorm( 1 , 0.1 ) ,
        b ~ dnorm( 0 , 0.3 ) ,
        sigma ~ dexp( 1 )
) , data=dd )

Construct the third model

m8.3 <- quap(
    alist(
        log_gdp_std ~ dnorm( mu , sigma ) ,
        mu <- a[cid] + b[cid]*( rugged_std - 0.215 ) ,
        a[cid] ~ dnorm( 1 , 0.1 ) ,
        b[cid] ~ dnorm( 0 , 0.3 ) ,
        sigma ~ dexp( 1 )
) , data=dd )

Plot the interaction

par(mfrow = c(1, 2))

# plot on the LEFT
# plot Africa - cid=1
d.A1 <- dd[ dd$cid==1 , ]
plot( d.A1$rugged_std , d.A1$log_gdp_std , pch=16 , col=rangi2 ,
    xlab="ruggedness (standardized)" , ylab="log GDP (as proportion of mean)" ,
    xlim=c(0,1) )
mu <- link( m8.3 , data=data.frame( cid=1 , rugged_std=rugged_seq ) )
mu_mean <- apply( mu , 2 , mean )
mu_ci <- apply( mu , 2 , PI , prob=0.97 )
lines( rugged_seq , mu_mean , lwd=2 )
shade( mu_ci , rugged_seq , col=col.alpha(rangi2,0.3) )
mtext("African nations")

# plot on the RIGHT
# plot non-Africa - cid=2
d.A0 <- dd[ dd$cid==2 , ]
plot( d.A0$rugged_std , d.A0$log_gdp_std , pch=1 , col="black" ,
    xlab="ruggedness (standardized)" , ylab="log GDP (as proportion of mean)" ,
    xlim=c(0,1) )
mu <- link( m8.3 , data=data.frame( cid=2 , rugged_std=rugged_seq ) )
mu_mean <- apply( mu , 2 , mean )
mu_ci <- apply( mu , 2 , PI , prob=0.97 )
lines( rugged_seq , mu_mean , lwd=2 )
shade( mu_ci , rugged_seq )
mtext("Non-African nations")
